<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99520994162878></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99520994162878><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99520994162878>RE: Help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99520994162878#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=65444><span id= >Tebyen</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>199 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jul 15th 11:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.84]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You can start buying spells at lvl 1. Get summon food, summon water, and summon dagger, and true north. None of the other lvl 1 spells are worth getting. At lvl 4, get your pet spells, starting with Elementalkin Earth. Your pets spells require a component, but i don't know what that is. Get summon bandages, and summon wisp if your race is night blind. Get gate and fire flux too. Go for cloth armour until you can afford better. You won't be able to earn much plat till lvl 10 if your near crushbone or lvl 12 if your near the Karanas. Hunt bandits for their sashes. As for the rest of the spells, always get the pet spells firt and foremost.<br>&nbsp;<br>Tebyen Trueheart(druid)<br>Frizza (enchanter)<br>Tebyene (ranger)<br>Proud member of Cold Comfort</td></tr>
