<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99503364397755></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99503364397755><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99503364397755>Hunting in Unrest</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99503364397755#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 13th 10:14 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've seen several posts about Unrest, ow it's good hunting. That is very true. However, I haven't seen any posts on details of hunting in Unrest. [Maybe you have, and I just haven't seen it. If so, sorry :-)]<br><br>Anyway,<br>lvls 9-12--Dangerous, but possible. You probably want to stick to death beetles in the LEFT yard, just watch out for house pulls going bad. There seem to be fewer creatures in the left yard, but there is a door on that side that people sometimes pull from, which WILL cause trains sooner or later. Just stay close to the wall opposite the porch and you will probably do reasonably well. Also, even though death beetles are not generally agressive, they WILL attack if you attack undead. You should probably know someone you know will be there at the same time you are because you can NOT solo and there is rarely ever anyone your level in the zone, in my experiance.<br><br>Lvls 13-15--Kill yard trash with a partner, you can take anything in the yard and the loot is getting better (amanita falloides, grave molds, rusties, and the occasional bronze weapon) Death beetles are still a danger, but you can avoid pulling too many if you're careful. Group members your level will still be rare though.<br><br>Lvls 16-20--Probably stick to first-floor pulls and possibly try the second floor if you feel particularly lucky and/or suicidal. You will want a  full group at first, but by 20 you can probably do first-floor pulls with just one other person.<br><br>Lvls 21-24--Second floor is probably your best bet, because the loot is good and the first floor is mostly mid-blue or green. The mobs drop fine steel and sometimes small bronze (YAY! P) Not having reached this level, I can't say a whole lot about this point on.<br><br>Lvls 25-27-- Any room in the house. Loot is same as second floor.<br><br>28+--The Basement. Killkillkill. Make trains. Have fun. Get great XP. Get great loot.<br><br>Kranken, gnome conjurer<br>&lt;Gnomish Liberation Army&gt;<br>ONE DAY GNOMES SHALL RULE NORRATH! (Till then, please watch where you put your feet? OW OW OW GET OFF MY FOOT!)<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
