	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a Gnome Mage and it is one of the best classes IV played! Most people say it&#8217;s hard to do the research for the pets and some spells but let me be the first to tell you its not! It just takes a little time and work but its not like killing a lvl 35 mob when you&#8217;re only lvl 16. No. If you think about it, it&#8217;s actually easy! The only not so great part is what if the researching fails. That will suck but there&#8217;s ways to get around that like doing the concordance of research quests or saving up you stat points and dumping them all into research. Since putting points into anything such as spell types or weapon skills is a waste then you should have plenty. That is what I did and I have a powerful awesome Mage. Here is a suggestion though. Get more than one of each component just in case. It&#8217;s better to be safe than sorry! Now I bet your thinking &#8220;Where do I find the components?&#8221; The site that will help you with this is www.Magecompendium.com! OK now lets make your first Mage! Here is what I did to start out my Mage.<br><br>Race &#8211; Gnome<br>Bonus Points &#8211; 25int, 5agi<br>Deity &#8211; Agnostic<br><br>Set up your Mage like that and you will have a safe and easy journey ahead of you. If you have any questions about Mages, you can e-mail me at Sadlyness@hotmail.com! <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
