<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99469279192218></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99469279192218><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99469279192218>RE: HELP</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99469279192218#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>385 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 9th 11:33 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.26]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here some tips:<br><br>1. Use your pet(duh)<br><br>2. Make sure you take off half of the mobs health with your direct damage spells, but not burning so fast that it comes and kills you.  If you don't do half the the damage you lose of the the exp. for the kill. <br><br>3. If you are outdoors and your pet dies and something is after you, hold CTRL while holding one of the direction movement keys, ie. the left or right arrow. This will make you strafe while you run, and will let you outrun many monsters if your health isn't below 2 bubbles. This also works wonders when dueling becuase you can kite your opponent around (unless they have snare or sow).<br><br>4. Killing a lot of blue cons will level you faster than killing red and yellow cons. This is not true at lower levels, but once you get to about level 16, it is.<br><br>5. Don't try to take on too much at once just becuase you think you are a big powerful mage. If you get in over your head, run or gate. Don't risk it and stay and try to fight.<br><br>6. Giving your pets rusty scythes, two-handed swords, and halberds will drastically increase their damage output at lower levels. <br><br>Hope that helps.<br><br>Former Everquest Addict that wants to play again.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
