<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99449858022670></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99449858022670><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99449858022670>RE: are we the best solo?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99449858022670#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jul 7th 5:36 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Druids, mages and necros all solo quite well in EQ.  This is a well known fact to most players.  Each class has its own +'s and -'s to soloing.  <br><br>I use this philosophy- soloing is destroying a MOB (or MOBs) at the least amount of time, mana and health expense.  <br><br>Yes, all classes are good at this tactic to one degree or the next but, none (in my opinion) can do it as well as the three classes mentioned above. Hence, soloing.  <br><br>I have tried all three classes and I must say I find (stressing I) the Mage to be the best at it.  One must understand that the Mage class was built around the use of a pet.  Try soloing a Mage without the pet and you'll understand very quickly what I mean.  <br><br>I have watched many Mages soloing and have found that they do not focus their soloing tactics on the pet, i.e. buffing pet with all available buffs or heals (Burnouts, DS's, Expedience, Renew Summons and so on).  Or, thinking out which pet is the best to combat a certain MOB a Mage may be hunting most frequently in a zone.  <br><br>Equally important is which DD's or AOE's to cast and at what times during a combat session to cast them.  Even the spot in a zone that a Mage chooses to base his or her soloing in is very important.  <br><br>Soloing is easy.  Soloing well is an art.<br><br>That is my opinion.  I'm not saying Necros and Druids are not good at soloing, they are.  I'm saying I have found the Mage to be the best (most efficient) at it than the other two classes.  Take it or leave it.<br><br>Alish Istari,<br>Level 30 Mage,<br>Brell       <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
