	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are losing a pet and getting a new one, you are doing it right.  Chain casting refers to using mana to summon pet after pet fo fight, but you can only have 1 pet at time.  Chain casting will not allow multiple pets.  I personally have not used the method other than practicing when switching pets.  It is a method intended/used mostly for higher levels; at 20 you shouldn't need to worry about it.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
